in the rest of the newspaper,

500
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,440
not even in the agony column.

501
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,480
We can't know it's from the Doctor.

502
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:00,160
Of course it's from the Doctor.

503
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:02,080
The Impossible Girl,
that's what he calls me.

504
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:04,520
He says lunch but not when or where.

505
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:08,920
On the other side.
The other side of London? Bit vague.

506
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:11,400
The other side of regeneration, perhaps?
Once he's recovered?

507
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:13,720
So what am I supposed to do?
Guess where we're meeting?

508
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:17,240
Perhaps that's the point.

509
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:20,520
Perhaps you're supposed
to prove that you still know him.

510
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:23,240
Think what that must mean for a man
who barely knows himself.

511
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:27,800
It doesn't makes sense, he doesn't
do puzzles. He isn't complicated.

512
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:30,280
He really doesn't have
the attention span.

513
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,520
So...

514
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:43,920
keeping it dead simple,
on the other side...

515
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,360
(SNIFFING)

516
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:33,120
(COUGHS)

517
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:35,360
What's wrong?

518
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:37,680
I don't know. Maybe the smell?

519
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:39,880
I know, it's everywhere.

520
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:42,640
Where did you get that coat?

521
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:47,560
(CLEARS THROAT) I bought it.

522
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:48,960
From where?

523
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:50,680
-Uh, a shop.
-No.

524
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,560
Might've been a tramp.

525
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:56,040
You don't have any money.

526
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:59,760
I... I had a watch.

527
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:02,320
No! That watch was beautiful.

528
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:03,680
It was my favourite.

529
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:07,280
You swapped your favourite watch for
that coat? That's maybe not a good deal.

530
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:10,160
Well, I was in a hurry,
there was a terrible smell.

531
00:34:10,240 --> 00:34:11,280
Okay.

532
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:13,120
(CHUCKLES)

533
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:17,560
No, no. Don't, don't...
Don't, don't smile.

534
00:34:17,640 --> 00:34:21,520
I will smile first and then
you know it's safe to smile.

535
00:34:21,600 --> 00:34:24,160
-Are you cross with me?
-I am not cross!

536
00:34:24,240 --> 00:34:26,520
But if I was cross,
it would be your fault and...

537
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:28,400
Yes, I am cross.

538
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:30,480
-I guessed that.
-I am extremely cross.

539
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:32,280
And if I hadn't changed my face,
would you be cross?

540
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:33,680
I would be cross if I wasn't cross!

541
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:35,840
-Why?
-Why?

542
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:41,320
An ordinary person
wants to meet someone that they know

543
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:43,480
very well for lunch, what do they do?

544
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:48,320
Well, they probably
get in touch and suggest lunch.

545
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,920
Mmm-hmm. Okay.

546
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:53,680
So what kind of person would put
a cryptic note in a newspaper advert?

547
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:55,000
Well, I wouldn't like to say...

548
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:56,360
Oh, go on, do, say.

549
00:34:56,440 --> 00:34:59,960
Well, I would say that that person
would be an egomaniac, needy,

550
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:02,640
game-player sort of person.

551
00:35:02,720 --> 00:35:06,960
(SIGHING) Thank you.
Well, at least that hasn't changed.

552
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:09,560
No, I don't suppose it ever will.

553
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:11,400
No, I don't suppose it will, either.

554
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:16,480
Clara, honestly,
I don't want you to change.

555
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:21,760
It was no bother, really.
I saw your advert,

556
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:24,280
I figured it out,
happy to play your game...

557
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:28,120
No, no. I didn't place the ad.
You placed the ad.

558
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:29,600
-No, I didn't.
-Yes.

559
00:35:29,680 --> 00:35:32,600
You placed the ad, I figured
it out, Impossible Girl. See, lunch!

560
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:34,040
No, look. The Impossible...

561
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:36,440
That is a message
from the Impossible Girl.

562
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:39,440
For the Impossible Girl.

563
00:35:43,240 --> 00:35:46,080
-Ooh.
-Ah. Hmm.

564
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:51,640
Well, if neither of us placed that ad,
who placed that ad?

565
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:55,840
Hang on. Egomaniac, needy game-player?

566
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:57,360
-This could be a trap.
-That was me?

567
00:35:57,440 --> 00:35:59,480
-Never mind that.
-Yes, I am minding that.

568
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:01,800
-Clara.
-You were talking about me?

569
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:05,560
Clara, what is happening right now,
in this restaurant,

570
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:07,640
to you and me, is more
important than your egomania!

571
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:09,160
Nothing is more important
than my egomania!

572
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:10,800
Right, you actually said that!

573
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:12,160
You never mention that again!

574
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:15,520
It's... It's a vanity trap.

575
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:19,360
You're so busy congratulating
yourself on solving the puzzle,

576
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:22,480
you don't notice that you're
sticking your head in a noose.

577
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:23,720
What are you doing?

578
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:27,040
And that isn't the only grey one,
if you are having a cull.

579
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:28,600
What, do you have a
problem with the grey ones?

580
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:30,600
If I got new hair and it was grey,
I would have a problem.

581
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:32,080
-Yeah, I bet you would.
-Meaning?

582
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:34,640
It's too short.

583
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:36,720
Ow!

584
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:39,920
Sorry, it was the only one out of place.
I'm sure that you would want it killed.

585
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:42,000
Ooh, are you trying to
tell me something?

586
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:44,360
I'm trying to measure
the air disturbance in the room.

587
00:36:45,160 --> 00:36:47,600
Right. Moments when
you know you are boring.

588
00:36:57,240 --> 00:36:58,800
There is something extremely wrong

589
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:00,440
with everybody else
sitting in this room.

590
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:02,200
Mmm, basically don't you
always think that?

591
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:03,880
Look at them. Don't look!

592
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,400
You just said to look!

593
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,320
Look without looking.

594
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:17,360
They look fine to me.
They're just eating.

595
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:20,520
Are they?

596
00:37:25,520 --> 00:37:27,000
(WHIRRING)

597
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:35,120
Okay, no. No, they're not eating.

598
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:37,480
Something else they're not doing.

599
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:43,320
Breathing.

600
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:45,520
(ALL WHIRRING)

601
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:51,880
What do we do?

602
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:57,920
-Well, you don't want to eat, do you?
-I've slightly lost my appetite.

603
00:37:58,160 --> 00:37:59,960
How long before
they notice that we're different?

604
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:01,280
Not long.

605
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:02,400
Anything we can do?

606
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:05,880
How long can you hold your breath?

607
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:10,600
We could casually stroll out of here,
like we changed our minds.

608
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:13,240
-Happens all the time.
-Of course it does.

609
00:38:38,280 --> 00:38:40,680
We could take another look at the menu.

610
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:52,160
What are they?

611
00:38:52,240 --> 00:38:55,200
I don't know. But don't worry,
because that's not the question.

612
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:58,000
The question is
what is this restaurant?

613
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,320
Okay, what is this restaurant?

614
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:00,440
I don't know.

615
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:12,800
Ah, no sausages.

616
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:17,880
And there's no pictures, either.
Do you have a children's menu?

617
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:22,280
Any specials?

618
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:23,800
(ROBOTIC VOICE) Liver.

619
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:25,720
I don't like liver.

620
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:30,080
Spleen. Brain stem. Eyes.

621
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:33,200
Hmm... Is there a lot
of demand for those?

622
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,600
I don't think that's what's on the menu.

623
00:39:37,680 --> 00:39:39,560
I think we are the menu.

624
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:42,200
Lungs. Skin.

625
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:45,240
Excuse me.

626
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:51,080
Okay. Robot in a mask.

627
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:52,600
It's a face.

628
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,360
Yeah, it's very convincing.

629
00:39:57,160 --> 00:39:58,480
No. It's a face.

630
00:39:58,880 --> 00:39:59,920
(YELPS)

631
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,000
Yes.

632
00:40:01,120 --> 00:40:04,840
-Yes, what?
-Yes, we have a children's menu.

633
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:07,480
(BOTH GASP)

634
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:09,880
(CLARA SCREAMING)

635
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,800
You've got to admire their efficiency.

636
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:14,280
Is it okay if I don't?

637
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:18,520
(BOTH SCREAMING)

638
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:24,880
(BOTH GRUNT)

639
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:31,440
Hello! Hello, are you the manager?
I demand to speak to the manager!

640
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:35,720
This is not a real restaurant, is it?

641
00:40:36,640 --> 00:40:41,600
Well, it's more a sort of
an automated organ collection station

642
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:44,400
for the unwary diner.
Sweeney Todd without the pies.

643
00:40:44,480 --> 00:40:45,680
So where are we now?

644
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:48,920
Factually, an ancient spaceship,
probably buried for centuries.

645
00:40:49,680 --> 00:40:52,680
Functionally, a larder.

646
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,640
So, why hasn't somebody come for us?

647
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:57,800
-We're alive.
-We're alive. In a larder.

648
00:40:57,880 --> 00:41:00,440
Exactly. It's cheaper than freezing us.

649
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:02,360
Okay.

650
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:03,760
Are you ready?

651
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:05,440
Go for it.

652
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:07,040
Don't let it roll away.

653
00:41:07,160 --> 00:41:08,160
No.

654
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:09,520
We've got one shot at this.

655
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:10,920
Next time, make one that doesn't roll.

656
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:13,000
Go!

657
00:41:17,240 --> 00:41:19,760
-Have you got it?
-I think I can just about reach it.

658
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:23,560
-It's at times like this I miss Amy.
-Who?

659
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:24,680
Nothing.

660
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:28,000
Ready?

661
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:29,720
Don't miss.

662
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:32,080
Oh!

663
00:41:33,040 --> 00:41:34,680
Ooh.

664
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,320
Sorry, did I hit something?

665
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:40,160
Oh, the symbolism!

666
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:48,840
You should make that thing
voice-activated.

667
00:41:49,720 --> 00:41:50,800
Oh, for God's sake. It is, isn't it?

668
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:52,240
I don't want to talk about it.

669
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,040
Doctor.

670
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:02,040
Dormant.

671
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:03,680
How do you know?

672
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:05,160
I don't. I'm just hoping.

673
00:42:08,880 --> 00:42:11,720
So, is it these guys
that killed the dinosaur?

674
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:16,320
Well, if they're harvesting organs,
a dinosaur would have some great stuff.

675
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:20,560
Why would robots need organs?
Burke and Hare from space?

676
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:22,840
Maybe. That's a good theory.

677
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:28,720
Droids harvesting spare parts.
Ah, that rings a bell...

678
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,520
Captain! My Captain!

679
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:42,200
Can he see us?

680
00:42:42,280 --> 00:42:43,280
Dormant.

681
00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:44,400
Hoping?

682
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:47,680
Yep. Oh, look! He's recharging.

683
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:51,880
He's asleep, doesn't even
know we're here.

684
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,000
Are you sure?

685
00:42:53,240 --> 00:42:54,800
Sure, not sure, one or the other.

686
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:58,840
Okay, so half man, half robot.
A cyborg, yeah?

687
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:02,080
-Oh.
-Oh?

688
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:04,360
-Ooh...
-Ooh?

689
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:06,840
Look at the hands.

690
00:43:07,080 --> 00:43:08,080
What about them?

691
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:09,600
-Look at them.
-I'm looking.

692
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:21,520
They don't match. These hands don't
belong to the same body.

693
00:43:24,080 --> 00:43:25,520
I don't understand.

694
00:43:25,600 --> 00:43:27,880
Oh, I don't blame you.

695
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:31,800
See this, this is not
your normal cyborg.

696
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:34,720
This isn't a man
turning itself into a robot.

697
00:43:35,640 --> 00:43:40,720
This is a robot turning himself
into a man, piece by piece.

698
00:43:40,800 --> 00:43:42,200
That's what the restaurant's for?

699
00:43:43,160 --> 00:43:45,160
Well, it would need a constant
supply of spare parts.

700
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:48,600
You can tan skin but organs rot.

701
00:43:48,680 --> 00:43:51,800
Some of that metal work, it looks Roman.

702
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:55,520
I wonder how long it's been around?

703
00:43:55,600 --> 00:43:58,440
How much of the original is even left?

704
00:43:58,520 --> 00:44:01,400
-The eyeballs look very fresh, though...
-Oh.

705
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:03,760
(GASPING)

706
00:44:12,080 --> 00:44:13,440
Is it awake?

707
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:17,600
It's waking up, I think.

708
00:44:21,920 --> 00:44:23,040
Okay, let's go.

709
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,120
(PANTING)

710
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:37,040
I've seen this before.
I'm missing something!

711
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:39,320
Doctor!

712
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:41,480
It's a brand-new head, rebooting.

713
00:44:41,560 --> 00:44:42,600
Come on!

714
00:44:42,680 --> 00:44:44,400
I've seen this before!

715
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:46,760
Oh! Hurry up. Get out.

716
00:44:51,200 --> 00:44:52,440
Doctor!

717
00:45:00,520 --> 00:45:03,400
Sorry, too slow. There's no point
in them catching us both.

718
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:05,000
Well, give me the screwdriver!

719
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:11,040
I might need it.

720
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:23,160
Oh, Doctor!

721
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:35,480
(SOBS)

722
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:12,960
DOCTOR: Something else
they're not doing.

723
00:46:13,120 --> 00:46:14,120
Breathing.

724
00:46:21,760 --> 00:46:23,720
How long can you hold your breath?

725
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:25,280
(INHALING)

726
00:48:07,920 --> 00:48:09,080
(EXHALES)

727
00:48:10,800 --> 00:48:11,880
(SIGHS)

728
00:48:14,280 --> 00:48:15,720
Bring her.

729
00:48:33,760 --> 00:48:37,280
All right, stop!
Stop! Stop it, all of you, now!

730
00:48:37,360 --> 00:48:39,000
BOY: Ha, it's her first day.

731
00:48:42,440 --> 00:48:45,440
If you don't stop it, I'm going to have
each and every single one of you

732
00:48:45,520 --> 00:48:47,200
kicked out of this school.

733
00:48:47,280 --> 00:48:49,400
Go on, then, do it!

734
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:53,440
(CLASS LAUGHING)

735
00:49:02,520 --> 00:49:04,040
Where is the other one?

736
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:14,760
There was another. Where is he?
Where is the other?

737
00:49:17,560 --> 00:49:22,440
You will tell us
or you will be destroyed.

738
00:49:24,560 --> 00:49:26,160
What did you say?

739
00:49:26,360 --> 00:49:27,400
You will tell us.

740
00:49:28,960 --> 00:49:31,040
Yeah, I know. Or what?

741
00:49:31,120 --> 00:49:32,400
You will die.

742
00:49:33,640 --> 00:49:36,080
Go on, then. Do it.

743
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:46,680
Go on, then.

744
00:49:48,960 --> 00:49:50,680
Do it.

745
00:49:53,080 --> 00:49:55,920
I'm not going to answer
any of your questions.

746
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:59,640
So you have to do it.
You have to kill me.

747
00:50:00,240 --> 00:50:02,680
Threats don't work unless you deliver.

748
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:08,240
You will tell us where the other one is.

749
00:50:08,320 --> 00:50:09,400
Nope.

750
00:50:09,560 --> 00:50:12,120
-You will be destroyed.
-Destroy me, then.

751
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:14,040
And if you don't,

752
00:50:14,120 --> 00:50:17,840
then I'm not going to believe a single
threat you make from now on.

753
00:50:18,160 --> 00:50:21,040
Of course, if I'm dead,

754
00:50:21,120 --> 00:50:24,440
then I can't tell you
where the other one went, then.

755
00:50:24,640 --> 00:50:27,840
You need to keep this place
down here a secret, don't you?

756
00:50:28,920 --> 00:50:31,080
Never start with your final sanction.

757
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:33,720
You've got nowhere to go but backwards.

758
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:40,120
Humans feel pain.

759
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:43,840
Bigger threat to smaller threat.
See what I mean? Backwards.

760
00:50:45,040 --> 00:50:48,360
The information can be extracted
by means of your suffering.

761
00:50:49,360 --> 00:50:51,360
Are you trying to scare me?

762
00:50:51,440 --> 00:50:54,200
Because I'm already
bloody terrified of dying

763
00:50:54,280 --> 00:50:57,560
and I will endure a lot of pain
for a very long time

764
00:50:57,640 --> 00:50:59,600
before I give up the information
that is keeping me alive.

765
00:50:59,680 --> 00:51:00,760
How long have you got?

766
00:51:10,200 --> 00:51:13,560
All you can offer me is my life.
What you can't do is threaten it.

767
00:51:13,640 --> 00:51:15,480
You can negotiate.

768
00:51:17,400 --> 00:51:20,640
Okay, okay, okay, okay. Yes, yes, yes.

769
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:24,880
I am crying and it's just because
I am very frightened of you.

770
00:51:24,960 --> 00:51:26,760
And if you know anything
about human beings,

771
00:51:26,840 --> 00:51:28,080
that means you...

772
00:51:28,160 --> 00:51:30,240
You're in a lot trouble.

773
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:34,000
We will not negotiate.

774
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:35,160
CLARA: You don't have a choice.

775
00:51:35,320 --> 00:51:37,880
I tell you what,
I'll answer your questions

776
00:51:37,960 --> 00:51:39,160
if you answer mine.

777
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:42,080
We will not answer questions.

778
00:51:42,160 --> 00:51:44,840
We'll take turns, I'll go first.
Why did you kill the dinosaur?

779
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:46,600
We will not answer...

780
00:51:46,680 --> 00:51:49,840
-Why did you kill the dinosaur?
-We will not answer questions!

781
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:52,760
Then you might as well kill me, because
I'm not talking again till you do.

782
00:51:54,920 --> 00:51:56,200
(SIGHS)

783
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:06,480
Within the optic nerve of the dinosaur

784
00:52:06,560 --> 00:52:09,240
is material of use
to our computer systems.

785
00:52:09,760 --> 00:52:12,800
You burned a whole dinosaur
for a spare part?

786
00:52:13,200 --> 00:52:15,040
No. Now, hang on.

787
00:52:17,080 --> 00:52:18,440
You know what's in
a dinosaur's optic nerve,

788
00:52:18,520 --> 00:52:21,000
which means you've seen them before.

789
00:52:22,160 --> 00:52:23,760
Where is the other one?

790
00:52:23,840 --> 00:52:25,960
How long have you been
rebuilding yourselves?

791
00:52:27,040 --> 00:52:29,040
Look at the state of you!
Is there any real you left?

792
00:52:29,120 --> 00:52:30,600
What's the point?

793
00:52:35,200 --> 00:52:37,120
We will reach the promised land.

794
00:52:39,000 --> 00:52:40,240
The...

795
00:52:40,320 --> 00:52:42,000
The what, the promised land?
What's that?

796
00:52:42,800 --> 00:52:44,480
Where is the other one?

797
00:52:46,720 --> 00:52:47,880
(EXHALES)

798
00:52:48,240 --> 00:52:49,360
I don't know.

799
00:52:52,560 --> 00:52:54,000
But I know where he will be.

800
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:56,760
Where he will always be.

801
00:52:59,080 --> 00:53:02,360
If the Doctor is still the Doctor,

802
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:06,200
he will have my back.

803
00:53:10,920 --> 00:53:13,520
(WHIMPERING) I'm right, aren't I?

804
00:53:13,600 --> 00:53:15,760
Go on, please, please,
God, say I'm right.

805
00:53:16,760 --> 00:53:17,760
(GASPS)

806
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:22,680
(EXHALES)

807
00:53:23,320 --> 00:53:27,360
Hello, hello, rubbish robots
from the dawn of time.

808
00:53:27,760 --> 00:53:30,760
Thank you
for all the gratuitous information.

809
00:53:31,080 --> 00:53:33,560
Five foot one and crying,
you never stood a chance.

810
00:53:34,280 --> 00:53:35,480
Oh, stop it!

811
00:53:38,840 --> 00:53:41,800
This is your power source
and feeble though it is,

812
00:53:41,880 --> 00:53:45,800
I can use it to blow this whole room
if I see one thing that I don't like.

813
00:53:45,880 --> 00:53:48,640
And that includes karaoke
and mime, so take no chances.

814
00:53:48,720 --> 00:53:52,240
See, Clara? That's how you
disguise yourself as a Droid.

815
00:53:52,440 --> 00:53:54,880
Yeah, well, I didn't have a lot of time.
I'd been suddenly abandoned.

816
00:53:54,960 --> 00:53:58,320
Yeah, sorry. No, actually I'm not.
You're brilliant on adrenaline.

817
00:53:58,400 --> 00:54:01,440
And you were out of your depth, sir.
Never try and control a control freak.

818
00:54:01,520 --> 00:54:03,520
I am not a control freak!

819
00:54:03,600 --> 00:54:04,600
Yes, ma'am.

820
00:54:04,960 --> 00:54:06,040
(WHIMPERS)

821
00:54:06,240 --> 00:54:08,800
-Why are you here?
-Why did you invite us?

822
00:54:10,520 --> 00:54:15,240
The message in the paper.
That was you, wasn't it?

823
00:54:21,640 --> 00:54:22,640
Oh.

824
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:25,680
I hate being wrong in public,
everybody forget that happened.

825
00:54:26,280 --> 00:54:28,080
-Clara, say the word.
-What word?

826
00:54:28,160 --> 00:54:29,520
They never sent you in here
without a word.

827
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:32,160
-I don't want to say it.
-I've guessed it already.

828
00:54:32,240 --> 00:54:34,000
BOTH: Geronimo!

829
00:54:44,440 --> 00:54:46,280
Remain still and lay down your weapons,

830
00:54:46,360 --> 00:54:47,880
in the name of the British Empire!

831
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:49,280
(YELLING)

832
00:54:50,360 --> 00:54:51,800
Strax!

833
00:54:51,880 --> 00:54:55,160
-Sorry.
-I've told you before, take the stairs.

834
00:54:55,320 --> 00:54:56,440
Oh, look. The cavalry.

835
00:54:56,520 --> 00:55:00,360
I burned an ancient, beautiful
creature for one inch of optic nerve.

836
00:55:00,440 --> 00:55:02,480
What do you think you can
accomplish, little man?

837
00:55:02,560 --> 00:55:04,240
What do you? Vastra?

838
00:55:05,440 --> 00:55:09,800
The establishment upstairs has been
disabled with maximum prejudice

839
00:55:09,880 --> 00:55:11,240
and the authorities summoned.

840
00:55:11,320 --> 00:55:12,760
CLARA: Hang on, she called the police?

841
00:55:12,840 --> 00:55:14,400
We never do that, we should start.

842
00:55:14,480 --> 00:55:16,960
You see? Destroy us if you will,

843
00:55:17,040 --> 00:55:18,920
they're still going to close
your restaurant.

844
00:55:20,560 --> 00:55:21,920
That was going to sound better.

845
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:24,480
Then, we will destroy you.

846
00:55:34,520 --> 00:55:36,040
No, you won't.

847
00:55:36,960 --> 00:55:39,160
You are logical. You have restraint.

848
00:55:39,240 --> 00:55:41,800
You kill to survive,
you're not a murderer.

849
00:55:41,880 --> 00:55:43,760
He's not a what?
This is a slaughterhouse.

850
00:55:43,840 --> 00:55:45,320
How does that make it different
from any other restaurant?

851
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:47,080
You weren't vegetarian
the last time I checked.

852
00:55:47,160 --> 00:55:50,040
This is over. Killing us won't change
that. What would be the point?

853
00:55:50,120 --> 00:55:52,000
To find the promised land.

854
00:55:52,080 --> 00:55:54,520
You're millions of years old,
it's time you knew. There isn't one.

855
00:55:54,600 --> 00:55:56,160
I am in search of paradise.

856
00:55:56,240 --> 00:55:59,480
(LAUGHS) Yeah? Well, me, too.
I'm not going to make it, either.

857
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:01,640
(GRUNTS)

858
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:02,840
Doctor!

859
00:56:03,080 --> 00:56:04,800
I will leave in the escape capsule.

860
00:56:04,880 --> 00:56:06,280
Destroy where necessary.

861
00:56:06,360 --> 00:56:11,000
Escape capsule? This ship is millions
of years old, it'll never fly.

862
00:56:11,200 --> 00:56:14,120
-It has been repaired.
-What with?

863
00:56:14,200 --> 00:56:15,520
You.

864
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:17,240
STRAX: Defensive positions, everyone.

865
00:56:19,920 --> 00:56:21,920
CLARA: Doctor! He's getting away!

866
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:25,080
Your friend is intelligent.
He'll know better than to follow me.

867
00:56:31,200 --> 00:56:32,960
(GROANING)

868
00:56:36,720 --> 00:56:39,120
Right, here we are, this is the place.
Come with me.

869
00:56:41,160 --> 00:56:42,960
It is our intent to leave.

870
00:56:43,040 --> 00:56:45,120
If it is your intent to stop us,

871
00:56:45,200 --> 00:56:47,760
perhaps we should get down to business.

872
00:56:52,200 --> 00:56:53,600
Dear Lord.

873
00:56:53,880 --> 00:56:55,400
What has she landed us with this time?

874
00:56:55,480 --> 00:56:57,040
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

875
00:57:00,600 --> 00:57:02,320
The restaurant is closed.

876
00:57:11,560 --> 00:57:14,880
Keep everyone out.
No one goes in there!

877
00:57:25,360 --> 00:57:26,760
What are you doing?

878
00:57:26,840 --> 00:57:29,520
I've got the horrible feeling
I'm going to have to kill you.

879
00:57:31,040 --> 00:57:33,840
I thought you might appreciate
a drink first.

880
00:57:33,920 --> 00:57:35,320
I know I would.

881
00:57:41,880 --> 00:57:43,520
(MACHINERY CLANKING)

882
00:57:46,640 --> 00:57:48,080
Watch out!

883
00:57:55,920 --> 00:57:57,320
Fifty-first century, right?

884
00:57:57,400 --> 00:58:00,840
Time-travelling space ship,
crashed in the past.

885
00:58:00,920 --> 00:58:02,880
You're trying to get home
the long way round.

886
00:58:04,280 --> 00:58:07,280
-I go to the promised land.
-So you keep saying.

887
00:58:09,160 --> 00:58:13,760
Okay, so your restaurant
is made out of your old ship.

888
00:58:14,640 --> 00:58:18,120
But you're wasting your time.
It can't ever fly.

889
00:58:18,760 --> 00:58:20,360
The escape pod is viable.

890
00:58:20,440 --> 00:58:24,120
How? You can't patch up
a spaceship with human remains.

891
00:58:24,200 --> 00:58:26,440
You know, this really is ringing a bell.

892
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:33,720
Okay, that's clever.

893
00:58:33,800 --> 00:58:35,000
How are you powering it?

894
00:58:36,320 --> 00:58:37,760
Skin.

895
00:58:47,800 --> 00:58:51,040
Get to the station. We need more men!

896
00:58:51,840 --> 00:58:53,880
What shall I tell them is happening?

897
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:55,640
Go on!

898
00:58:56,200 --> 00:58:57,880
How many do you estimate, my dear?

899
00:58:57,960 --> 00:59:01,240
More than upstairs, about 20, 307?

900
00:59:01,600 --> 00:59:05,040
The ones upstairs were mere decoys.
These are battle-ready.

901
00:59:05,120 --> 00:59:07,360
I anticipate a challenge.

902
00:59:07,560 --> 00:59:08,920
(STRAX LAUGHING)

903
00:59:09,320 --> 00:59:11,440
Don't worry, my boy,
we shall die in glory!

904
00:59:11,520 --> 00:59:14,280
Okay, good-o!

905
00:59:24,560 --> 00:59:26,480
"SS Marie Antoinette.”

906
00:59:27,600 --> 00:59:31,240
Out-of-control repair droids
cannibalising human beings.

907
00:59:31,320 --> 00:59:35,240
I know that this is familiar but
I just... I just can't seem to place it.

908
00:59:35,320 --> 00:59:36,760
How would you kill me?

909
00:59:37,160 --> 00:59:40,160
Sister Ship of the Madame de Pompadour.

910
00:59:43,080 --> 00:59:44,920
Nope, not getting it.

911
00:59:45,760 --> 00:59:47,520
How would you kill me?

912
00:59:47,600 --> 00:59:49,360
Why don't you have a drink first?

913
00:59:49,440 --> 00:59:51,080
It's only human.

914
00:59:51,240 --> 00:59:54,200
-I am not human.
-Neither am I.

915
00:59:55,160 --> 00:59:56,920
STRAX: Why can't you stay dead, coward?

916
00:59:59,040 --> 01:00:00,040
(GRUNTS)

917
01:00:11,120 --> 01:00:12,680
DOCTOR: What do you think of the view?

918
01:00:17,160 --> 01:00:20,080
-I do not think of it.
-I don't think of it. I don't.

919
01:00:20,960 --> 01:00:22,760
Droids and apostrophes,
I could write a book.

920
01:00:22,840 --> 01:00:26,960
Except you are barely a droid any more.

921
01:00:28,080 --> 01:00:30,400
There's more human in you than machine.

922
01:00:33,200 --> 01:00:37,520
So tell me,
what do you think of the view?

923
01:00:49,880 --> 01:00:51,120
It is beautiful.

924
01:00:51,200 --> 01:00:54,440
No, it isn't. It's just far away.

925
01:00:54,520 --> 01:00:56,440
Everything looks too small.

926
01:00:56,520 --> 01:00:58,880
I prefer it down there.
Everything is huge.

927
01:01:00,040 --> 01:01:04,320
Everything is so important.
Every detail, every moment.

928
01:01:04,400 --> 01:01:06,440
Every life clung to.

929
01:01:07,320 --> 01:01:08,880
How could you kill me?

930
01:01:08,960 --> 01:01:10,680
For the same reason
that you're asking me that question,

931
01:01:10,760 --> 01:01:12,680
because you don't really
want to carry on.

932
01:01:16,120 --> 01:01:17,960
What'll happen to the other
droids when you die?

933
01:01:18,040 --> 01:01:19,480
You're the control node, aren't you?

934
01:01:19,560 --> 01:01:21,320
Presumably they'll deactivate.

935
01:01:22,520 --> 01:01:25,480
I will not die.
I will reach the promised land.

936
01:01:25,600 --> 01:01:27,480
There isn't any promised land.

937
01:01:27,560 --> 01:01:31,120
This is just... It's a superstition
that you have picked up

938
01:01:31,200 --> 01:01:33,600
from all the humanity
you've stuffed inside yourself.

939
01:01:33,680 --> 01:01:35,280
I am not dead!

940
01:01:37,120 --> 01:01:39,240
You are a broom.

941
01:01:40,720 --> 01:01:44,360
Question, you take a broom,
you replace the handle

942
01:01:45,680 --> 01:01:47,920
and then later you replace the brush.

943
01:01:48,000 --> 01:01:50,360
And you do that over and over again.

944
01:01:50,440 --> 01:01:51,760
Is it still the same broom?

945
01:01:51,840 --> 01:01:55,520
Answer, no, of course it isn't.
But you can still sweep the floor.

946
01:01:55,600 --> 01:01:57,520
Which is not strictly relevant,
skip that last part.

947
01:01:57,600 --> 01:02:00,960
You have replaced every piece of
yourself, mechanical and organic,

948
01:02:01,040 --> 01:02:03,200
time and time again.

949
01:02:03,280 --> 01:02:06,080
There's not a trace
of the original you left.

950
01:02:07,000 --> 01:02:09,760
You probably can't even remember
where you got that face from.

951
01:02:17,480 --> 01:02:19,800
-(CLATTERS)
-It cannot end.

952
01:02:21,040 --> 01:02:23,720
It has to. You know it does.

953
01:02:23,800 --> 01:02:24,920
And there's only one way out.

954
01:02:25,000 --> 01:02:27,320
Self-destruction is against
my basic programme.

955
01:02:27,400 --> 01:02:29,160
Murder is against mine!

956
01:02:31,880 --> 01:02:33,160
(GROANING)

957
01:02:37,960 --> 01:02:39,440
(GRUNTING)

958
01:02:41,160 --> 01:02:42,160
Jenny!

959
01:02:43,560 --> 01:02:46,560
Hold your breath! They're stupid,
everybody hold their breath.

960
01:03:05,640 --> 01:03:08,000
JENNY: I can't do it. I can't.

961
01:03:08,080 --> 01:03:13,000
VASTRA: Be brave, my love.
I can store oxygen in my lungs.

962
01:03:13,360 --> 01:03:15,520
Share with me!

963
01:03:21,080 --> 01:03:22,320
(GRUNTS)

964
01:03:24,440 --> 01:03:27,920
-You are stronger than you look.
-I'm hoping you are, too.

965
01:03:28,000 --> 01:03:30,360
This is over.

966
01:03:31,720 --> 01:03:34,480
Are you capable of admitting that?

967
01:03:35,200 --> 01:03:37,240
Do you have it in you to murder me?

968
01:03:37,480 --> 01:03:42,080
Those people down there,
they are never small to me.

969
01:03:42,520 --> 01:03:45,960
Don't make assumptions about
how far I will go to protect them,

970
01:03:46,040 --> 01:03:47,880
because I've already come
a very long way.

971
01:03:48,120 --> 01:03:52,000
And unlike you, I don't expect
to reach the promised land.

972
01:03:58,640 --> 01:04:03,640
You realise, of course, one of us
is lying about our basic programming?

973
01:04:06,480 --> 01:04:07,760
Yes.

974
01:04:07,920 --> 01:04:10,240
And I think we both know who that is.

975
01:04:23,760 --> 01:04:25,040
Stop!

976
01:04:26,120 --> 01:04:27,280
(GASPING)

977
01:05:07,280 --> 01:05:08,320
Whoa.

978
01:05:15,680 --> 01:05:17,520
You're sure he'd come back here?

979
01:05:17,600 --> 01:05:19,960
There was no trace of him
in the wreckage.

980
01:05:20,040 --> 01:05:23,280
They searched all of Parliament Hill.
Where else would he go?

981
01:05:28,280 --> 01:05:30,800
I fear we have missed him.

982
01:05:40,520 --> 01:05:42,200
Please, come in.

983
01:05:44,320 --> 01:05:46,320
I'm... I'm not interrupting?

984
01:05:46,600 --> 01:05:48,960
I should be glad of your company.
What can I do for you?

985
01:05:49,040 --> 01:05:51,840
Ah, well, that's exactly
what I was going to ask you.

986
01:05:52,600 --> 01:05:54,000
Seems like I'm stuck here now.

987
01:05:54,680 --> 01:05:56,040
Got a vacancy?

988
01:05:57,760 --> 01:06:00,520
You would be very welcome
to join our little household.

989
01:06:00,600 --> 01:06:05,200
But I have it on the highest authority

990
01:06:05,280 --> 01:06:07,520
that the Doctor will be
returning for you very soon.

991
01:06:07,600 --> 01:06:09,320
Whose authority?

992
01:06:10,320 --> 01:06:13,240
The person who knows him
best in all the universe.

993
01:06:13,600 --> 01:06:15,040
And who's that?

994
01:06:16,480 --> 01:06:18,800
Miss Clara Oswald,

995
01:06:19,880 --> 01:06:24,440
who, perhaps has, by instinct,
already dressed to leave?

996
01:06:24,520 --> 01:06:26,440
I just wanted a change of clothes.

997
01:06:30,760 --> 01:06:32,960
I don't think I know
who the Doctor is any more.

998
01:06:35,080 --> 01:06:36,080
(WHOOSHING)

999
01:06:38,040 --> 01:06:40,760
It would seem, my dear,
you're very wrong about that.

1000
01:06:41,960 --> 01:06:43,320
Clara!

1001
01:06:44,360 --> 01:06:46,160
Give him hell. He'll always need it.

1002
01:07:07,320 --> 01:07:08,720
You've redecorated.

1003
01:07:08,800 --> 01:07:10,120
Yes.

1004
01:07:10,200 --> 01:07:12,960
-I don't like it.
-Not entirely convinced myself.

1005
01:07:13,040 --> 01:07:15,400
I think there should be more
round things on the walls.

1006
01:07:15,480 --> 01:07:18,120
I used to have lots of round things.
I wonder where I put them?

1007
01:07:31,360 --> 01:07:35,600
I'm the Doctor.
I've lived for over 2,000 years

1008
01:07:36,120 --> 01:07:37,960
and not all of them were good.

1009
01:07:39,520 --> 01:07:41,400
I've made many mistakes

1010
01:07:42,600 --> 01:07:45,200
and it's about time
that I did something about that.

1011
01:07:49,040 --> 01:07:50,840
Clara, I'm not your boyfriend.

1012
01:07:52,160 --> 01:07:55,000
I never thought you were.

1013
01:07:55,080 --> 01:07:57,840
I never said it was your mistake.

1014
01:07:59,520 --> 01:08:01,080
(WHOOSHING)

1015
01:08:03,480 --> 01:08:04,960
What do you think?

1016
01:08:15,720 --> 01:08:18,600
-Who put that advert in the paper?
-Who gave you my number?

1017
01:08:18,800 --> 01:08:20,240
A long time ago, remember?

1018
01:08:20,320 --> 01:08:22,200
You were given the number
of a computer helpline

1019
01:08:22,280 --> 01:08:24,600
and you ended up phoning the Tardis.
Who gave you that number?

1020
01:08:24,680 --> 01:08:26,400
The woman. The woman in the shop.

1021
01:08:26,760 --> 01:08:30,720
Then there's a woman out there who is
very keen that we stay together.

1022
01:08:34,000 --> 01:08:35,360
(THUD)

1023
01:08:36,000 --> 01:08:37,720
How do you feel on the subject?

1024
01:08:40,800 --> 01:08:42,760
Am I home?

1025
01:08:42,920 --> 01:08:44,760
If you want to be.

1026
01:08:49,600 --> 01:08:50,800
I'm sorry.

1027
01:08:53,080 --> 01:08:54,840
I'm so, so sorry.

1028
01:08:56,480 --> 01:08:59,200
But I don't think I know
who you are any more.

1029
01:09:01,920 --> 01:09:03,840
(MOBILE RINGING)

1030
01:09:07,360 --> 01:09:09,520
You'd better get that.
It might be your boyfriend.

1031
01:09:10,400 --> 01:09:14,120
Shut up. I don't have a boyfriend.

1032
01:09:23,120 --> 01:09:24,160
Hello?

1033
01:09:27,760 --> 01:09:29,760
-Hello?
-ELEVENTH DOCTOR: It's me.

1034
01:09:29,920 --> 01:09:31,360
Yes, it's you, who's this?

1035
01:09:31,800 --> 01:09:35,480
It's me, Clara. The Doctor.

1036
01:09:41,480 --> 01:09:42,880
What do you mean, "the Doctor"?

1037
01:09:44,040 --> 01:09:46,440
I'm phoning you from Trenzalore.

1038
01:09:47,040 --> 01:09:49,480
-I don't...
-From before I changed.

1039
01:09:50,160 --> 01:09:55,320
I mean, it's all still to happen for me.
It's coming. Oh, it's a-coming.

1040
01:10:02,120 --> 01:10:03,600
Not long now.

1041
01:10:04,280 --> 01:10:07,600
(SIGHS) I can feel it.

1042
01:10:15,400 --> 01:10:18,240
Why? Why would you do this?

1043
01:10:18,920 --> 01:10:21,680
Because I think
it's going to be a whopper.

1044
01:10:22,640 --> 01:10:25,400
And I think you might be scared.

1045
01:10:26,000 --> 01:10:30,720
And however scared you are, Clara,
the man you are with right now,

1046
01:10:31,000 --> 01:10:33,000
the man I hope you are with,

1047
01:10:34,040 --> 01:10:39,280
believe me, he is more scared than
anything you can imagine right now.

1048
01:10:39,840 --> 01:10:43,640
And he... He needs you.

1049
01:10:46,200 --> 01:10:47,680
So who is it?

1050
01:10:47,760 --> 01:10:49,200
Is that the Doctor?

1051
01:10:49,400 --> 01:10:50,880
Is that the Doctor?

1052
01:10:52,440 --> 01:10:53,680
Yes.

1053
01:10:54,240 --> 01:10:57,920
He sounds old.
Please tell me I didn't get old.

1054
01:10:58,000 --> 01:10:59,800
Anything but old!

1055
01:11:00,400 --> 01:11:01,520
I was young.

1056
01:11:02,760 --> 01:11:05,320
Oh! Is he grey?

1057
01:11:07,480 --> 01:11:08,480
Yes.

1058
01:11:10,560 --> 01:11:13,840
Clara, please, hey? For me?

1059
01:11:14,680 --> 01:11:17,880
Help him. Go on.

1060
01:11:19,920 --> 01:11:23,200
And don't be afraid.

1061
01:11:33,680 --> 01:11:35,280
Goodbye, Clara.

1062
01:11:39,600 --> 01:11:40,720
Miss you.

1063
01:11:50,240 --> 01:11:51,240
(SNIFFS)

1064
01:11:51,800 --> 01:11:53,160
Well?

1065
01:11:55,840 --> 01:11:57,560
Well what?

1066
01:11:57,640 --> 01:11:59,200
He asked you a question.

1067
01:12:01,120 --> 01:12:02,320
Will you help me?

1068
01:12:02,440 --> 01:12:05,200
You shouldn't have been listening.

1069
01:12:05,480 --> 01:12:08,240
I wasn't. I didn't need to.
That was me talking.

1070
01:12:14,240 --> 01:12:18,160
You can't see me, can you?
You look at me and you can't see me.

1071
01:12:19,800 --> 01:12:21,520
Have you any idea what that's like?

1072
01:12:25,000 --> 01:12:27,520
I'm not on the phone, I'm right here.

1073
01:12:29,760 --> 01:12:31,600
Standing in front of you.

1074
01:12:34,600 --> 01:12:36,080
Please, just...

1075
01:12:38,480 --> 01:12:40,160
Just see me.

1076
01:13:03,320 --> 01:13:04,560
Thank you.

1077
01:13:05,480 --> 01:13:06,640
For what?

1078
01:13:07,200 --> 01:13:08,640
Phoning.

1079
01:13:14,840 --> 01:13:18,280
(STAMMERING) I don't think
that I'm a hugging person now.

1080
01:13:19,040 --> 01:13:21,040
I'm not sure you get a vote.

1081
01:13:22,320 --> 01:13:23,800
Whatever you say.

1082
01:13:24,760 --> 01:13:26,600
This isn't my home, by the way.

1083
01:13:27,320 --> 01:13:30,920
Sorry, I'm sorry about that. I missed.

1084
01:13:32,520 --> 01:13:35,080
-Where are we?
-Glasgow, I think.

1085
01:13:35,160 --> 01:13:38,360
Ah, you'll fit right in. Scottish.

1086
01:13:40,400 --> 01:13:42,400
Right, shall we, uh...

1087
01:13:44,360 --> 01:13:49,400
Do you want to go and get
some coffee or chips or something?

1088
01:13:49,480 --> 01:13:50,880
Or chips and coffee?

1089
01:13:51,400 --> 01:13:54,520
Coffee. Coffee would be great.
You're buying.

1090
01:13:55,280 --> 01:13:56,800
I don't have any money.

1091
01:13:56,880 --> 01:13:58,200
You're fetching, then.

1092
01:13:59,360 --> 01:14:01,360
I'm not sure
that I'm the fetching sort.

1093
01:14:01,520 --> 01:14:04,520
Yeah, still not sure you get a vote.

1094
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:17,000
(WHIRRING)

1095
01:14:20,160 --> 01:14:21,560
Hello!

1096
01:14:25,000 --> 01:14:27,800
I'm Missy. You made it!

1097
01:14:28,320 --> 01:14:31,320
I hope my boyfriend
wasn't too mean to you.

1098
01:14:33,600 --> 01:14:34,960
Boyfriend?

1099
01:14:35,040 --> 01:14:38,560
Now, did he push you
out of that thing or did you fall?

1100
01:14:39,080 --> 01:14:40,320
I couldn't really tell.

1101
01:14:40,840 --> 01:14:45,240
He can be very mean sometimes.
Except to me, of course.

1102
01:14:45,320 --> 01:14:48,160
Because he loves me so much.

1103
01:14:49,520 --> 01:14:51,640
I do like his new accent, though.

1104
01:14:52,120 --> 01:14:53,680
I think I might keep it.

1105
01:14:56,240 --> 01:14:57,480
Where am I?

1106
01:14:58,600 --> 01:15:00,000
Where do you think you are?

1107
01:15:00,760 --> 01:15:03,760
Look around you. You made it.

1108
01:15:03,960 --> 01:15:08,800
The promised land. Paradise!

1109
01:15:10,320 --> 01:15:14,520
Welcome to Heaven!

1110
01:15:31,760 --> 01:15:34,440
-Where the hell have you been?
-It's not my fault, I got distracted.

1111
01:15:34,600 --> 01:15:36,960
-By what?
-You can always find something. Come on!

1112
01:15:37,720 --> 01:15:40,200
CLARA: Where are we going?
DOCTOR: Into darkness.

1113
01:15:40,680 --> 01:15:43,000
Welcome to the most dangerous
place in the universe.

1114
01:15:47,600 --> 01:15:49,160
They're coming! They're coming!

1115
01:15:49,400 --> 01:15:50,880
Aristotle!

1116
01:15:51,120 --> 01:15:53,120
The enemy are right on top of us!

1117
01:15:54,160 --> 01:15:55,240
I'm sorry.

1118
01:15:55,400 --> 01:15:58,880
Exterminate! Doctor!

